This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with improving neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel method for improving translation quality using a machine learning approach. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing an intelligent system for language translation. The paper also uses neural networks, which could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions using image captioning as a test domain, which could potentially place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
